reviews: A lovely hotel! Perfect for a family trip to Paris. Slightly away from tourist area in a nice quiet area. Only a few subway stops away from main attractions. We all loved it & hotel staff were very helpful.

The hotel is located in a quite side street. Boulangeries (coffee), butchers, fruit & vegetable shops, supermarkets, restaurants and a metro line are within five walking minutes. There is also parking in a garage of a nearby hospital; however the garage was closed due to late arrival (21:30). Staff member Orely drove around with us in the car until we found street parking. That was very helpful as we otherwise would have been lost and would not have known the meaning of the many signs. It was a hiccup that was taken care of.

Nice place in Paris. Good location close to two metro stations and close to most important things to see in Paris. Friendly staff and nice room size (strange for Paris hotels :-) )
Good french breakfast and good coffee in room. Bottle of water every day in room.
I can recomend the Fred Hotel for short stay in Paris.

Not sure how this place had good reviews. As a world traveler this place had very deceiving pictures & filthy rooms. Their panoramic room views would make a bug look large and the shower stalls/toilet/floors never cleaned.. cobwebs & layers of scum visible on stalls. Rotating staff indifferent because they are fully aware. Breakfast not worth it and a few old bottles of alcohol on table considered their bar? Go elsewhere.

Really liked the hotel. One problem was with the smell of room deodorant in the downstairs area - where breakfast is served. Hotel was not able to provide any gluten free options so we didnt take breakfast there

My wife and I stayed at The Fred in August and found it very comfortable. The staff were very friendly and accommodating. It is a great area as well with the many nice restaurants within walking distance. The Metro station is also close by for exploring the rest of Paris

Over the last week I have stayed in 4 hotels, 2 in Paris and one each in London and Perpignan. Fred Hotel was the one I enjoyed the most. It was full of colour and modern art and design. When i'm in Paris this will be my first choice.

We arrived at the hotel late in the evening. We were three people: two adults and a child. for a child we were asked to pay 20 euros to get an extra bed. we paid. but the bed they brought us was broken. in the end, it was decided to put the child on the floor, and we were promised a refund upon departure (20 euros for the first night). the next day, we were moved to a triple room. for which, too, was paid 20 euros. upon check-out, the man at the reception with glasses (looks like a Spaniard) spoke in a raised voice, did not want to return 20 euros for the first night. and that the child was forced to sleep on the floor. also, did not want to discuss delicately the problem. spoke in parallel on the phone with someone (obviously not on working moments). When I started filming his behavior on my phone, I immediately got scared. I left this conversation with tears in my eyes. do not recommend, some staff are not trained to communicate with guests

The reception person's quite friendly and helpful, helped us to upgrade the room for free. In a quiet neighborhood, the metro station is within walking distance. If you find hotels near the business district expensive, can try those located in the residential area like this one.

We had 2 rooms for 5 nights at the Fred Hotel. The staff were friendly and helpful. The rooms were spotlessly clean and comfortable. The location was good, being only a short walk to the nearest Metro station.
We would definitely stay there again.

This is a nice small boutique hotel in a quiet location but conveniently located with the metro being only a few minutes walk away, the Eiffel Tower was about 10 mins by cab and other main sites are easily reachable by the metro within 15-20 mins. Hotel was very clean, the room was nice and spacious (we had a deluxe room on the top floor, the only downside was the transparent glass door to the bathroom). Friendly staff and very welcoming, highly recommend.

Stayed here last year in November and theyve maintained the same level of hospitality and service. This time, we booked a classic room and requested an early check in. We waited at least an hour and was accommodated at 2pm with a bigger room and a patio. We felt safe around the neighborhood and being close to Plaisance, we can get access to almost everywhere in minutes via Metro.

Stayed in the Fred hotel for 3 nights from the 10th June. We had 2 rooms booked- the superior double. We had originally booked the basic double but we were contacted by the hotel management to say that these rooms wouldn't be suitable for 2 people sharing and the superior double would be better for more space.

We got to the hotel early and Tovo took our luggage and recommended places to go while we waited for the rooms to be ready. There is a big supermarket- Auchan just around the corner which was great! And the main plaicence metro station was a 2 minute walk which took us every where we needed to go!
One of the rooms we got was lovely and big with a king bed and separate bathroom with bath/shower, the other room we were allocated was alot smaller with a sink in the middle of the room and a bad layout with only a double bed. The only downside was the room size and the fact that the shower water leaked everywhere in the bathroom and bedroom. Personally I think that the 2 rooms were very different and should not have been charged at the same price.

The Air com system was brilliant and well needed as it was a very hot weekend when we stayed. The staff were friendly and attentive and we would definitely stay here again if visiting paris again.

While it is certainly not as fashionable a locale as some other parts of town, I love this quiet little area. Easy access to the Mtro, a couple of markets, solid restaurants, and third wave coffee, just a few minutes from the Gare Montparnasse.

We really enjoyed staying at the Fred Hotel. The location is great - near 2 subway stops and many restaurants and shops. The hotel is clean and the rooms are pleasant. The thing that made our stay special was the care and kindness of the staff.

This hotel was everything I needed for a trade show visit. Good value, super clean and friendly. Rooms and especially beds very comfortable, felt homely but chic.

Area is lovely, not too busy and some wonderful shops, cafes and restaurants. Really chilled and seemed quite French and residential.

The hotel is in a good location, a couple of minutes walk from a metro station (Plaisance or Pernety) with good connections into central Paris. The staff were really friendly, and the room spacious and extremely comfortable - we felt immediately at home. It was relatively quiet at night. The breakfast was good, although the room was a little small for all the guests. Highly recommend!

The hotel is excellent value for money. Small and small rooms ( like all in Paris) but well decorated.The front desk clerk accommodated an early checkin in a smaller room and I later moved to the room I had originally booked.Everything is spotless new and clean,breakfast is very good. It has a small cozy waiting area with a couch and magazines in the front part of the breakfast room. My only comment is that the shower does not retain the water on the floor ( ask for extra towels)I definitely recommend it and will go back when in Paris

Stayed here for 2 nights. Liked the room, not too large but contained everything you could need for a short stay. Very friendly people at reception, helpful and professional.

Location is also very good, with lots of restaurant choices in walking distance, metro around the corner and not too much noise from traffic.
Also luggage storage with a numbered ticket is a good practice you don't see often with hotels in this price class.

Highly recommended.

We just returned from Paris this week and stayed at the Fred Hotel. While the accommodations were mediocre at best, the service (or lack thereof), at the front desk from Gerard was absolutely appalling. He was completely rude and appeared to be somewhat racist with his disposition and approach with me and my family. The original room that I was assigned, upon arriving at the hotel, was not the room that I had booked - a superior room - it was the basic room and the black tiles were loose and dirty in the shower. Overall, the standard room to which I was originally assigned - room number 55, did not appear clean. Gerard offered the superior room to me as if presenting an alternative as a concession after I complained, however, this was the room that I had booked in the first place! Also, Gerard asked me to pay for my stay in advance at my arrival for the entire amount. I am a very seasoned traveler and have never been asked to pay for my hotel stay in its entirety in advance at check-in. Also, my first day there, Gerard had a verbal disagreement that devolved quickly and got quite nasty with a loyal hotel guest who had stayed there at least five times previously. I was shocked at how rude he was to this guest who was an older woman who attempted to engage Gerard with only civility and respect. All of the other employees, including the other people who worked at the front desk and the housekeepers, were very gracious and polite. I have been to Paris numerous times - my father is French and I grew up part-time in France - and only booked here because I needed to be somewhat close to Orly Airport but still wanted to stay within the city limits (inside the priphrique ). Also, my daughter and I stayed in room 51 and the lock on our room door was always jammed and we actually got locked in our room one morning - this was a major fire hazard and I needed to call from inside of our room to have someone come and let us out of the room. On our check-out day, this past Sunday, September 5th, I needed to print out our boarding passes and Covid test results prior to our flight and the printer was not working and unavailable. I think that the corporate office should review Gerard's employee record and performance. I would never book the Fred Hotel again and would not recommend this hotel to anyone.

Great hotel in a great location near very nice places to eat and shop, close to metro for getting around, wonderful professional and friendly staff, Rooms extremely clean and very up-to-date, nice breakfast in the morning with coffee, breads, meats, cheeses, cereals, fruits. Great hotel!

Next to metro station, nice beds, AC. No fridge in rooms, small elevator. Nice French breakfast: baguettes and croissants. Lot of restaurants around. We stayed on the top floor, in some parts of the room the ceiling was tight, with beams, but still a nice room.

A collegue and I were in Paris for work for several days. When we arrived, everything was ready and the hostess was really welcoming. We were agreably surprised by the practicity of the location : pretty closed from the metro and tramways.The rooms were perfect, nothing to add. Perhaps, just a thing about the shower, not entierly closed, which splah water all over the bathroom !
Breakfast and bar are served in a cozy and comfortable atmospehe, right next the chemney. good quality and origin products.

Very friendly service personnel and nice rooms .
I gotta say Fred Hotel excellence my experience. The service was very friendly and helpful . The breakfast was also fresh , lots of choices and quality items. I was pleased by their location which has good connections.
I will be happily return on my next visit to Paris.

Stayed for 3 nights as a group of four, booked two family rooms which worked well. Located at the end of the corridor on floor 4, we were able to close a door on the hallway and leave our bedroom doors open in order to make one huge apartment.

Walking distance to bakeries and restaurants this is a great find. Metro station near by that can take you to all the Parisian landmarks.

Staff were fantastic and couldn't do enough for us, very friendly, accomodating and knowledgeable.

For parking, we parked at the hospital in which the hotel can get you a discounted rate to park.

Highly recommended and will return. In the words of the great Arnie himself, 'I'll be back'

We arrived having booked a room for 3 adults, I think there had been some confusion as it took a long time to get a room, and when we did it was very small, we did get moved to a better sized room for the second & third night. The rooms are a bit tatty, bed side table coming away, glass rolled off and smashed. Showers dont have a position which doesnt soak the entire bathroom, but not your head :). But overall hotel was okay and location was perfect. Lovely shops & restaurants/ cafes and easy walking to various stations and metro stops, as well as into the city.

A small scale hotel, surrounded by many cafes, and restaurants about 5-10mins walking distance. The main floor lobby is very modernly designed. There is an option of buffet breakfast although this wasnt included with my stay. The room was kept very clean each day. Free Nespresso coffee was provided in your room, as well as a free bottle of water per day. Staff was very friendly and courteous. You are required to pay a small city taxes fee per night. We stayed in a superior room and standard room, I would recommend a luxury room for more space.

A lovely hotel a bit off the beaten path. Still easily accessible by metro. Small with about four rooms per floors. Very quiet. Good service from all the staff. Things to know: the rooms on the last floor have low cellings. No showers but this is well described on their website. The breakfast was ok. This was the main thing that was ok (versus excellent).

Bottom line : now on my short list when I go to Paris.

Impeccably decorated and super clean. It's conveniently located one small block from a subway station.The staff is friendly and efficient. If you are going to Paris and don't know your way around, know this: this place is a great choice. It's the little things though (no pun intended). The bed When they say it's a KING size bed, it's rather on the line of "little" king size bed. The breakfast situation is where it gets a little complicated. It's not about the quality of what is offered. Everything is there, everything is nice. Tables are tiny though. I find the "concept" toaster, coffee machine and egg boiler kind of difficult to get. Some instructions would be in order. For the life out of me I couldn't make that thing spit out coffee instead of hot water. But this would be totally irrelevant if only they had AN EXTRA PERSON on the floor clearing the tables and available for issues like this. THe only person they have would be gone for sometimes 20 minutes. I understand, there's probaly plenty to be done in the kitchen but that affects the breakfast experience in my opinion. The first day I honestly thought someone hadn't shown up for work, but on the second day it became clear that they were simply short staffed. That being said, the place is great. Youll have a peaceful. night's sleep in a safe, clean and pleasant place. Breakfast may be turbulent but you'll be fed. I would both recommend and go back there.

ordered this hotel for ridiculous overpriced rate and got a tiny room with dirty blanket and broken sink and broken shower head. The location is very far from all of the known activities.
The room was a Deluxe Room with courtyard views, where we had to suffer from party noise until 2AM from one of the flats next to it. We could not sleep due to the loud music.
The only advantage is the nice staff in the hotel.
I was very disappointed, and this is not my first time in Paris.

it was a very nice weekend in Fred Hotel. The service was very friendly and helpful and the Hotel esthetical and comfortable. The breakfast was also very nice. My girlfriend and me were pleased by this inspiring location.

I had a great experience at the Fred Hotel. Staff was very welcoming and friendly. The rooms were nicely made up and provided me with everything I needed. The location is great - it's just off a busy street so that it wasn't very crowded but close enough that I could walk to local cafes for breakfast.

A clean hotel with friendly staff. We stayed for 5 days while we toured around Paris. It's in a pretty good position for this. The nearest metro station is a few minutes walk away (Plaisance ) and only 20 mins ride most of the main sites of interest; Champs Elyssee, Eiffel Tower Last louvre etc. The staff are all very helpful and friendly. All the reception guys speak good English.
Breakfast is continental style self service. It can get a little crowded but all on all not bad. In the local area there are several bars, restaraunts, take aways, wine shops and a small supermarket so you can easily cater for any food needs nearby. A short cab ride into the centre of the Montparnasse area will put you in the way of many good Brasserie.
Next time we are in Paris I will check the availability here first.

the hotel is welcoming.
the room are modern with very good sleeping.
The service always available and people ready to help.
i really appreciate the location none far from transport, with restaurants and shops nearby.

Highly Recommended ! Very Comfortable and Clean Rooms backed by a very Professional and Friendly Staff at the Reception. Very close to the Metro and a variety of Restaurants in close proximity. Ideal stay for a business traveler or family.

The staff were very friendly and helpful. The hotel was very quiet, and a good size, so it never felt overcrowded. The breakfast was very nice, and the breakfast room was clean, organised and relaxed. Also, location is perfect, not on a busy ride, only a couple minute walk to the train station that takes you very close to the middle of Paris. And lovely restaurants in the area as well.

Great value hotel located in a beautiful part of Paris. Quiet with good local shops and restaurants yet still easy to get to all the sights. Hotel with modern decor nice rooms and good value breakfast. Very friendly staff.

A cool little boutique hotel that is easily accessible to many parts of Paris. Friendly welcome and lovely staff. The place is clean and a good base of you are visiting Paris. The reception area also has a tv and seating area.

Choosing this hotel was strongly based on reviews, as we stayed only a regular weekend in Paris which tends to be over quite fast.
I liked the style a lot, and I would also recommend this hotel to everyone else on a private trip as well! For sure during the summer days the hotel is probably very full and not as affordable as during our stay in early May, but totally worth a visit it if you have the chance.

We are checking out now from Fred hotel. It feels like leaving home. We were a family of 5. The location is perfect the metro at a walking distance. The street full of bakeries and restaurants. These rooms are big small but very well equipped, clean and the bed is very confortable. The breakfast includes high quality products. But above all was the service. Everyone here was more then welcoming , helpful, extremely friendly. Was very good choice staying with u at Fred hotel. Highly recommended

I really didnt want to give Fred hotel any reviews esp a negative one as our stay there was mostly okay (convenient location etc.) but the way Mr. Tovo at the front desk handled our checkout was simply appalling. He claimed that we hadnt paid for the stay (we were charged by the other nice gentleman when we checked in), when we pulled up our Amex transaction record to show him proof of payment (hotel name, address, DATE and amount etc.) he dismissed us by saying how do I know it was for this trip?. Yup you read it right! He basically called us liars! Then he decided to confirm with the other gentleman who had checked us in by calling him. All this time we were standing there like idiots for no fault of our own. After his confirmation (because ofcourse Amex and the whole world apparently goes around lying!) he gave a fake apology. This gentleman does not belong in hospitality industry.

The other gentleman who checked us in was the opposite and extremely nice but we will not be coming back.

An small but excellent hotel tucked in one of the sidestreets of the 14th arrondisement, we were lucky to have stumbled upon it on the net. It is newly renovated, clean and well-maintained. The air-conditioned rooms were a definite plus during the heat wave that swept Paris during our stay. The staff was friendly, efficient and very helpful. I would stay here again, if ever I return to this city!

I only stayed for a couple of nights but I found the hotel very good. The room was comfortable and well equipped although as a preference I would chose tea over coffee in the room.
The staff were friendly and helful if needed.
A food quality accomodation for a reasonable price.

our stay was short but the staff was really attentive.especially Ader (?) at the front desk.My wife was ill and his kindness, genuine concern was reassuring...little things were done to acommodate..i will definitively recommend this hotel to anyone : clean, well located with excellent people working there

This was a good find. The concierge were very friendly and helpful. Especially Yusuf who made our interactions a delight. It's in a great location with a few good brasseries close by and multiple subway stations a short walk away. The room was very small though. Very small. But the trade off for a good hotel in the centre of Paris was worth it.

Spent 3 nights at Fred. My review is mixed. As a hotelier myself; I can forgive a lot as I know the drill but others require intervention by higher management. The main requirement for me is friendly and welcoming staff which Fred certainly has. Everyone was all smiles. Sadly that where it ends

I wont complain of room not being ready for early check-in as thats just a bonus. I will complain of a faulty room and no follow up despite my daily complaints to front desk whom all said we will take care of it...... perhaps they did and couldnt fix it so ignored it. Im not sure. But as a hotel departmental manager, leaving your quest questioning or ignoring is the absolute worse thing you can do. Sadly this is what happened at Fred. I stopped complaining. I was told they would fix my issue and if not complete a room move. Issues wasnt fixed. ......no complaint logged on my account. No notes for room move.

To be honest the issues were pretty mediocre and didnt really affect me as I was hardly in my room ....... however if I was then I wouldve been escalated to the GM.

Thanks Fred for the friendly smiles but sorry; wont be back

My husband and I stayed at the Fred Hotel for three nights in December. We were able to check in early which was wonderful, and we were brought to a room on the main level in the back garden area. Our room did not have any windows, but had a glass door/ entrance with a shade over it. The room itself was well appointed with an area for a desk, a nespresso machine and a small television. The bathroom was quite large for a paris hotel, however the door to the bathroom was a clouded glass. This was not my favorite, as it did not provide much privacy while using the toilet. We had a comfortable stay at the Fred hotel and it was very reasonably priced for Christmas time when other hotels were rather expensive. We did find that our room had been left unlocked after it was cleaned one day, and that was rather unsettling. The front desk was always very friendly and helpful. About a 10 minute walk to the local metro station.

Great little hotel in a nice quiet location.

Rooms were clean and tidy with decent bathrooms.

Close to the metro but walkable to all of the big tourist sites.

Never used the breakfast offering as we preferred to find a cafe nearby.

We would definitely recommend this hotel.

Stayed at the Fred Hotel for business and enjoyed the stylish Classic Room although it was rather small. The reception and breakfast area was beautiful but sometimes too cold due to the entrance and the very cold winter weather outside. Location was ok, Metro station close by. Staff was very kind. Thank you for having us.

Small but cute hotel. Stylish, quite, firm beds, smaal but clean rooms. Staff friendly, helpful and knowledgeable of local area and bilingual. Plenty of local eateries and shops to keep oneself amused for an evening or two.

Hotel was nice, just the lighting could have been a bit better. Room is small but is normal for being in Paris.
The only thing I didnt like was that you have to leave your key at the desk whenever youre leaving the hotel. But hey I guess you can never loose your key. Desk attendants were also very nice.

The stay was amazing. Very nice, modern boutique hotel. The staff made our stay fantastic. Tovo checked us in and pretended not to speak English. Made us practice our French and made for a funny joke. He was awesome and helped with ANYTHING we needed. Helder was just as awesome. He gave us great recommendations and we spoke several times. These two were fantastic and really helped make our anniversary trip special.

Thanks Fred Hotel

We recently stayed our 1 night in Paris at Fred Hotel. Cute and charming but the best part was the friendliness of the staff. As an American, you hear about the rude Parisians but they did not get the memo. They get Five stars from us. The breakfasts small but
delicious with fresh bread replenish throughout the morning. Clean rooms and was very quiet. Bonus is how close they were to the metro. Thank you Tovo for your hospitality.

Very charming hotel in nice safe area. Two metro lines are close by. The best thing in hotel are employs, very very friendly and willing to fulfill all requests we had. Check in and check out was easy and fast. Lobby is very nice, rooms could be a bit better. Breakfast was good, and worth the money, although area for breakfast was a bit small. I will definitely come back.

T`was a great stay with Mom and Dad, On a quiet street,near to a Metro, Restaurants, Cafe, and a large grocery few steps from the hotel. Excellent and welcoming staff who were helpful about anything! Overall a lovely botique hotel.

Very friendly and helpful staff, nice breakfast, the rooms were clean and comfortable
and I liked the fact that it is a non-smoking hotel
I liked the modern decoration!! Also the prices were affordable
I would totally recommend it!!!

Convenient hotel to the metro with great restaurants, especially for crepes! Modern hip room decor and big bed, but super tiny bathroom! Moderate size elevator, nice back patio garden, and cool lobby.

My stay at Fred Hotel was very pleasant. The staff were friendly and helpful, the rooms were clean and cozy, and the breakfast was fresh and affordable. I recommend this hotel for couples looking for a nice local taste of Paris.

The Fred hotel had very friendly hosts. They were welcoming and helpful from the first moment. There is a very small lift, 2 people max, and the room is quite small, but is really all you need. The AC was nice as it was a very hot weekend and it was nice to have coffee in the room too. We didnt need anything else for our quick stay. The 13 line is right around the corner and also there is a great breakfast shop just near the entrance to the metro where we had the best breakfast all week!

Great hotel and amazing front desk staff. They made an effort to speak in English and I really appreciate that. I was extremely happy that my room and bathroom was sparkling clean. I enjoyed my stay at Fred Hotel, thank you!

First, I cannot say enough about how welcoming the staff was every time we returned. Helder, the desk attendant, was so much fun to chat with! He put us at ease and recommended great food (very close).
Our rooms were small but very clean with clean bathrooms. Lovely windows with views of Paris rooftops. Shops of all kinds are all around this hotel and the neighborhood is quiet. We slept well, in spite of jet lag!
Showers/bath a bit odd in that they spray the water around the bathroom. We did have problems with wi-fi and even when it worked it would frequently bump us off.
All in all this hotel is so charming and comfortable. Thanks, Fred Hotel and Helder!!!

Read a lot of positive reviews of this hotel, so gave it a go for our 3 day Paris break. The hotel itself is tucked down a side street in the Montparnasse district (14th Arrondissement) which is a lovely area to walk around with cafe bars, delis, cheese shops, wine shops etc. It is close to the Metro for easy access to the city centre or a taxi to the main sites will be around 15 euro. The hotel is very well appointed, with lovely, compact rooms and a fabulous organic breakfast. Staff are very helpful and speak excellent English (our French is not up to much!). There is a lovely outside Terrace for guest use. We really enjoyed our stay - highly recommended!

The hotel was ok. A little out from the main tourist area of Paris, although only 2 blocks from the subway. Great French bakery around the corner. The room was small but that was expected for Paris. The bathroom sink kept clogging and the shower floor was kinda gross, work flip flops to shower. Probably wouldn't stay again....but was a pretty inexpensive.

I was traveling for work from the US to Paris for two weeks with my girlfriend. I needed a place that was convenient to get into the city and close to public transportation but would break the bank during peak seasons. Fred Hotel fulfilled all my needs and was better than I imagined! First off the staff is top notch and speak English very well. This is a huge deal because there can be a language barrier in France. Second they are very close to the M13 line and a half hour travel from every major attraction. Third the room was a good size and the bed was big enough for two people. This hotel was a great find and I would recommended them to friends. Thanks Fred for a great stay and putting up with the late nights stumbling in.

We staid for work for 5 days and had a room with extra space (advice from other reviews). That was a good choice! The room was quiet(6th floor), spacious enough, clean, with all the amenities (hair drier, internet, a large desk, some hangers and space to open the luggage, air condition,safe). The bathroom was spacious enough. Breakfast was standard continental. The only small issue we had was that the service can be improved: 1) room service always forgot something small eg. shampoo was empty (refillable shampoo was appreciated though!) or towel missing, 2)one morning we head to miss breakfast because it was not ready on time, etc. Overall a nice stay in Paris and conveniently located close to transport possibilities!

Really enjoyed the Fred Hotel. Boutique style, in a 6 floor building, we were at the top in what must have been an artist's garret, a long time back. Very well appointed room with two beds, modern bathroom etc. Breakfast was served in the ground floor dining room by pleasant staff. Well located with Metro stations within walking distance. Would stay again.

Greated by friendly staff, the Fred Hotel is a conveniently located , just few minutes walk to the metro stations .
Room is well equipped with good ventilation. Quiet surroundings contributed to a good night of sleep.
Value of stay in Paris !

My stay at this hotel was very pleasant, definitely recommend and will stay here again whenever Im in Paris. Really close to restaurants and cafes, two entries to the metro and the front desk is super helpful if you have any questions.

I had to stay in this district due to a friend that lives nearby. They suggested this hotel as it was close and very clean.
Upon late arrival I was checked in by the night staff. The rooms are nicely done but are very small. Overall, a very nice and pleasant stay!

Decent location near Alesia and Pernety metro. Polite, friendly and helpful reception. Clean room with stylish furnishing. Would highly recommend for those on reasonable budget. Overall we had a good experience.

Hotel is very simple and has nice decor. In a very convenient area with 2 metros very close by. The staff are very friendly and helpful and the room is cleaned daily. Downside is that we got the smallest sized room for the weekend and the shower in the room is a wet room situation where the water basically floods the whole toilet. A bit of a hazard as I slipped quite a few times after the shower. The noise level within the hall is very loud and if unlucky you can hear loud individuals voices in their room. Fortunately we could only hear this once in a while and nothing during the night. Great stay for a short weekend.

As family we were lucky to stay at Fred hotel. The location is great and safe. The team at front desk were helpful and polite. The rooms were big and clean with comfy beds.metro was access able and close. The salon was very cozy making us feel at home with the fire place We recommend the hotel and to reserve as early as possible.

I stayed again at this modern hotel boutique last December 2017...this time for about a week...and again it was a very pleasant stay. The room is big enough and very comfortable for somebody that use it mostly for sleeping, since one is mostly roaming around the city visiting all kind of interesting places. The bed was very comfortable, very clean room, with nice toiletries. They have breakfast available with excellent quality products/food. The hotel is strategically located close to fresh food stores, restaurants, metro (subway), etc. in a very secured area, so one can go in and out any time day and night. The staff was very courteous and handled any request i had promptly and efficiently. Special thanks again to the managers Mr.Tissa and Mr. Syilvio for their excellent customer service!

This hotel is located rather central in Paris, with good metro connections. The price is reasonable and the room was, even if it was at the smaller side, good. Beds were comfortable and everything was clean and tidy. The breakfast buffet was surprisingly good with a broad variety to almost all tastes. I do recommend this hotel.

Small boutique hotel not too far away from Montparnasse and a number of decent dining places. Very traditional.. rooms have still keys with heavy large keychain. On the other side a fairly modern hotel with a cozy lobby also for breakfast. Rooms are not really big. Sink is in the main room, shower and toilet in the bathroom.
Hotel is clean and area not too noisy, So great place to stay.

The hotel staff were hands down the friendliest and most welcoming staff!! Room and bathroom both a good size and exceptionally clean. Metro stop is a very short walk away even though it was a bit crazy trying to do the metro in a wheelchair. Monoprix at the end of the street so great for getting lunch and heading out for a day seeing the city. Hotel is in a quiet safe area. Great Korean restaurant a few streets away called Sodam. Would I stay again? Without a doubt!

Staff were the highlight of this place. They were kind and considerate, always had time to talk and get us a taxi if we needed it. The room was clean and comfortable, brilliant size given we had asked for a superior suite. Even a nespresso machine which was a lovely touch! Gorgeous bathroom, lovely lounge, and we loved the Montparnasse neighbourhood. Very bohemian! Easy access to the metro, plenty of places to eat. We loved it. Would definitely go back!

Staff is extremely accomodating, rooms are clean and nicely furnished. If you fear noise from the elevator do not take room 01. Room 11 has its own little deck. Good quality/ price ratio. Will definitely go back to this hotel

A hidden gem located at a well equipped neighbourhood with supermarket, pharmacy and nearby a few metro stops away from the one best croissant stalls in paris. Its not too far away from the effiel tower and also within a 20 min bus ride to the lourve. Kudos to the helpful staff at the hotel who are always ready to help. I am very appreciative of the service for me and my fiancee's stay at the hotel. The beds are comfortable and good tv system. A few points for feedback, for the bath tub maybe the glass panel could be slightly wider so that the water wont splatter over when one is using the shower and also have some instructions on how to set the tv to english audio will be helpful for tourist like me. Thank you and keep up the good work.

We arrived very late in the evening for our two night stay at the Fred Hotel. We were welcomed warmly. We loved our room on the top (6th) floor. The beds were very comfortable. The bathroom was clean. There was a store right around the corner. The neighborhood is delightful, full of little shops and cafes. The staff was very accommodating and kind. They even let us borrow an umbrella for a day when it was raining. They also loaned us plates and silverware so that we could eat our breakfasts in the room every morning from what we bought at the store around the corner. However, you can eat breakfast in their little dining area for a few euros. The metro is only 2 blocks away. I would recommend this hotel and I would stay there again. Thank you Fred Hotel. You were fabulous!

Just returned from a 4 night stay at the Fred Hotel. Room was clean and tidy, small but adequate with everything you require for a city break. Staff were fantastic and spoke English well. They assisted us with our travel plans, bookings and recommendations for dining. Felt staff went over and above their duties to help us. Would definately recommend.

We picked Fred Hotel as it was in an area of Paris we had not stayed in before. From the pictures online we expected to like the modernity...We were not disappointed then when we arrived we were warmly welcomed.by the Reception staff...We met four individuals and all tried to make to feel "at home". For travellers the main issue is Bed/sleep quality "Excellent", next is bathroom facilities the double sized shower was a special item that worked wonders in our estimation. Full stocked with all appropriate items....far better than average ! Cleanliness was also first-class. So Great Value all round..There is a room by room renovation underway.

Fred hotel is located in an exciting neighborhood in Paris 14th endorsement. The neighborhood is quiet and safe. The hotel is located close to the metro, going to the Eiffel or Louvre is just a small metro trip away.

Tasty and inexpensive meals are available in the surrounding area. I would recommend the Italian restaurant close to the hotel.

The staff and manager at Fred know the true value of customer service, they will help you with any issues you are encountering during your stay in Paris.

The property was modern, aesthetically pleasing and kept extremely clean. Front desk staff is very friendly and welcoming.
The rooms are modern, open and have the amenities you would expect. The bed is comfortable.

I recommend this hotel to everyone, who is looking for an enjoyable stay, great food, and excellent hospitality in Paris.

The hotel is an awesome place, staff are very helpful n always willing to go above and beyond,and they all speak English so it's perfect for the people who can't speak French or just a little, I stopped for a long weekend n it was brilliant perfect location and it's only a stones throw away from the metro, I'm booking for next year and would recommend it to anyone it's a perfect hotel n it's one off the best three star places I've ever stayed in

So how much you like this hotel depends on which type of room you get. The is basically small, medium, and large. Frugal at first I went with the Small version and this was a mistake, at least for me. I was here for 7 night stay and the room was barely large enough for the bed, 5 strides across and only 3 deep. Understated to say it was small. This is not my first trip to Europe so I was accustomed to quite small rooms and elevators, but this one fell within the lowest 10% I recall seeing.

But the front desk folks there are very friendly and helpful and eventually got me the large version for 30 more. For the size, this was a much more workable size room. The bed was firm and adequate even if not "enveloping" like some are. Good night's sleep was had every night.

Bathroom was sufficient sized although the arrangement of the shower head was a little screwy. Breakfast was typical European, nothing really hot.

One big concern is security and to that two points. First, my Safe was locked when I checked in, went down to front, the guy pulled a box out of a desk drawer and had me open in under 2 minutes. While I was grateful to get the safe open, this was just way toooo easy. Second was basic room access. Here these guys are still working in a 20th century mindset. Mechanical keys are used and are tied to a large key ring with the number indicated on the end. Coming back after my first day back a new person was at the front desk, never had seen me, and all I needed to obtain the key was the room number, no ID, nothing. I kept the key on my person the rest of my stay.

So I'd likely not stay here again for the reasons cited.

stayed here for 5 nights, had a cute and modern yet very tiny room. the staff was super friendly and breakfast was good as well. location was really nice and quiet. walking distance to metro, cafes, restaurant and other shops. definitely recommended! :)

For one week, my fiancee and I stayed at this small but cosy hotel. The rooms were quite tiny but nicely decorated and quite modern. The staff was extremely nice even though we do not speak French. The neighbourhood where the hotel is located is quiet and less seemingly less touristic than more central neighbourhoods. Also, it's quite close to the Tour Montparnasse

Sweet place, well appointed room, it would have been great if a fridge was available in the room but it's ok. Nice neiborhood, the parking is a little too expensive but we could let the car till the second afternoon and it was good.
The host boy didn't precise we couldn't take the car the evening and it should be precised.
Everyone was kind and friendly that's great.
Little accessories like shampoo or the coffee machine were also very good.
We had a very good stay at this hotel.

We stayed at the Fred for 7 nights. Hotel staff was professional and friendly. Our room was clean and modern. We had a great stay. The only complaint I have is that the doors to the rooms are very close to each other so you can hear all neighbors coming in an out.

Had a good time staying in Fred hotel. Neighborhood is calm and nice. Shops nearby. Not having a minifridge in the room was a minus because there were +35 celsius outside and cold drinks would be nice. Metrostop just around a coner. The hotel tax was not included and you have to pay it when leaving. It said on the website it is included so that was a bummer.
Nice and clean, modern small rooms.

I chose this hotel because I like boutique hotels and this one has I believe the smallest rooms I ever been . The rooms are nice, modern but very small, you can barely move inside if you're staying with someone else in the room, maybe the best option is to stay alone in this hotel.
The neighborhood is not very nice and not much to look around, but it has a metro station two blocks away in case you need to transport to the Paris tourist areas.

The premium room i had booked wasn't available so got down graded to a standard room which was OK but small - I was offered a half bottle of champagne as compensation (no good for a non drinker)

Room wasn't as clean as i would have hoped / expected & toilet hadn't been flushed properly since the last guest (not nice). Flies buzzing around the room combined with the fact that you can't control the temperature of the Air conditioning means i won't be going back in a hurry.

The room was spotless and decorated very nicely. I loved the area which is a bit outside of the main tourist area but very close to a Metro stop and even though it was our first time in Paris, we found it very easy to get around. On a budget, we chose the smallest room and it was perfectly sized for the two of us. Compact and very neat, the only thing I would caution on this room is that the bathroom door is glass (frosted but you still can see through it lol!). As long as you are comfortable with each other, it's not a problem and we have stayed in many small hotels where we figure out how to give the other a bit of needed privacy! The staff was exceptionally good and helpful. We enjoyed our stay here and will return in the future!

Fred Hotel was reasonably priced, clean, and friendly. The staff was multi-lingual and very helpful. They went above and beyond to take care of us--and new us on sight from day one. Rooms are not large, but clean, comfortable, and functional. Parking is non-existent, so be prepared to fight for Paris street parking if needed.

An excellent 7 days accommodation, in this boutique hotel, really felt like home! A real value for money, as everything was much better than expected from a 3 stars hotel! Efficient, professional and friendly personnel in the reception, concierge, housekeeping. As we visit Paris frequently, we truly believe that we have found our home, in Paris!

This was a perfect weekend get away stay. The hotel rooms were quit spacious for Paris. We stayed in a room on the ground floor with a small court yard attached. It was decorated beautifully in quite a modern way. Dark colors, natural wood, with bright colors to add a bit of contrast. Breakfast was simple, and yummy. The bed was extremely comfortable and the room as well as the bathroom very clean. As a frequent traveler to Paris this is quite impressive. The area is a quiet one with a few places to eat around but easy access to the metro will take you anywhere in a few minutes. Overall the staff was not often present and there was quite a wait to be checked in but nothing terrible. I would absolutely stay again and recommend to anyone.

Rooms are clean and neat.

If you are a tourist, like me, its a little out of the main area. Well I chose this consciously for the cost and a good deal I got online. Rooms are smaller than what it appears in the photographs. Very little place remains to walk around in the basic rooms. Its close to a couple of metro station. A little difficult to get to the main streets if you don't know the French language. It is a little far from the main happening streets of Paris. I stayed for a couple of days. Recommended to stay close to Eiffel or in the surrounding architecture area of Paris if you have limited number of days.

For the price this was an extremely nice hotel. Far from everything but if you can figure out the metro line your in luck! It's next to a station and it's very convenient. The neighborhood is very nice and quite....cute little shops everywhere. Amazing cheese and bakery down the street must go! (Sadly I can't remember the names as I write this ) I would stay here again! Ps. Just a side note if you're traveling from the US you need to know rooms in Europe are not large they are much smaller. Just an FYI

wonderful, helpful, polite staff. Quiet location. Neighborhood is quiet and there were very few tourists. the subway is steps away and it is easy to get anywhere from Fred Hotel.
there was a small, cozy lounge with different books and newspapers, magazines.
The breakfast had nice selection of fresh bread, fresh pastry, fruit, tea, coffee, juice, sliced meat, eggs, everything. More than enough (and I have a pretty good appetite).
The room was pretty big, comfortable bed.
Elevator and stairs.
Nice restaurants nearby opened late.
Bathroom big. Only thing there are no handles to get in and out of shower so that could be a bit slippery getting in and out.
Also, my room did not have any overhead shower but the handheld type that I have still not figured out how to use without getting the entire floor soaked.
Otherwise, a perfect place to stay.

We stayed in a premium room on the sixth floor, it was clean, comfortable, and and we appreciated the Nespresso coffee machine and good array of toiletries.

The room was very quiet, we had three excellent nights of sleep and awoke thoroughly refreshed to explore Paris.

We didn't have the breakfast but the breakfast area looked cosy and we overheard some positive comments about it. A lovely fire roared in the lobby area during the evenings which was a very pleasant place to sit with a drink.

The staff were polite, hospitable, knowledgable and welcoming; we had one minor query which was dealt with promptly.

The location was in a vibrant area with plenty of bars, patisseries and everything in between. The Hotel Fred is about a 30 minute gentle stroll or five minutes on the Metro to get to some of the main tourist sights and it was nice to stay in and walk around an authentic part of Paris away from the tourist traps.

When we return to Paris we would definitely consider the Hotel Fred which we thought was very good value for a very nice place to stay.
